            <p>Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform JavaScript runtime environment that allows developers to execute JavaScript code outside of a web browser. It is built on the V8 JavaScript runtime engine, the same engine that powers Google Chrome. Node.js enables the development of server-side and networking applications, and it has become widely adopted for building scalable and high-performance web applications.</p>
            <p>Node.js is designed to be asynchronous and event-driven, making it well-suited for handling concurrent operations and scalable network applications.</p>
            <p>NPM is the default package manager for Node.js and is used to install, manage, and share packages (libraries and tools) written in JavaScript.</p>
